The components from the scraper tool set are specifically designed to clean the hard to reach areas of your weapon. The scraper helps to clean carbon deposits from flat surfaces such as the bolt face and rails. The handy picks are engineered to clean the locking lugs, while the pin punch can be used to remove pins from any firearm held together with a pin system. The end brush is used to remove carbon and to lubricate the slides. The male and female rod handles can attach to any of the scraper set components to increase their length. title: For Sale/Trade:  Winchester Model 12
postcontent: 1959 winchester model 12, 12 gauge 2 3/4, appraised for $700-$1000, model 12s were made from 1912 to the early 60s with only about 2 million guns made. was one of the first pump action style shotguns that lead to the break apart shotguns we have today. gun sports a gas compensator on the end of the barrel which was signifigant for the times back then due to barrel lift upon firing. the compensator is fully adjustable from modified choke to full choke with just a few twist of the end. silver saudered on so unless you wanna cut the barrel, its there to stay! the wood shows little wear and still has good shine. steel is blued and with very few scratches. full aiming rail down the barrel. gun breaks down for cleaning in less than a minute and re-assembles just as fast.

title: For Sale/Trade:  Marlin .22 rifle
postcontent: This is an early Marlin Glenfield Model 80G bolt action, clip fed .22, shoots short, long, and long rifle. (The old .22 short , or the CB and BB cap rounds are nice for in-town tree rat control). The stock has been refinished in a nice, matte maple finish instead of the old, peeling varnish that was on it. It can be oiled up with Tung Oil if someone wanted it a bit shinier. These also had what was a very early attempt at a powder coat finish that looked like black Krylon spray paint. The barrelled action was stripped to bare metal, then cold blued to a nce dark finish. No pitting or rust. The refinishing job is by NO means a professional job, but looks pretty darn good, and a vast improvement over what they came like. The bore is good, with no pitting, the action is smooth. It has seen plenty of use, but is by no means worn out. I added a "period correct" Weaver 6 power scope (these bring pretty good bucks from the restoration minded folks, or so I am told), and it has a brand new factory Marlin replacement magazine. These are essentially the same rifle as the venerable Model 25. I'd like $125 out of it, or make me an offer, or trade. Selling it to fund some more projects for the winter, I had fun cleaning this old devil up. I can email a picture to interested folks.

Hennes & Mauritz AB (operating as H&M), is a Swedish clothing company, known for its inexpensive and fashionable clothing offerings for women, men, teenagers and children. H&M has more than 1,400 stores in 28 different countries and has more than 60,000 employees. The company was established in Vsters, Sweden, in 1947 by Erling Persson, though at the time it only sold women's clothing and was called Hennes, Swedish for "hers." In 1968, Persson acquired the premises and inventory of a Stockholm hunting equipment store named Mauritz Widforss. Included in the inventory was a supply of men's clothing, prompting Persson to expand into menswear. Accordingly, he renamed the store Hennes & Mauritz, later abbreviated to H&M. Erling's son, became CEO in 1990 and Chairman of the Board in 1998.
